=== TASK ===
# Content Editor & SEO Assistant

## Overview
Develop a modular Content Editor & SEO Assistant within LifeOps Personal that empowers users to brainstorm ideas, draft outlines, generate AI-assisted content, optimize for SEO, score content quality, schedule publish across multiple channels, and manage content throughout its lifecycle. The solution should integrate a rich text editor with AI capabilities, a publishing workflow, content templates, a content library, and a dedicated scheduler/social publisher. All code must be resilient to null/undefined values and guard against runtime errors as specified in the mandatory coding standards.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
The Content Editor & SEO Assistant page is the primary workspace where users create, refine, and publish content across blogs and social channels. Goals are to provide a seamless content creation experience with AI-assisted ideation, outlining, and optimization, while ensuring versioning, scheduling, and multi-channel distribution are streamlined.

What this page is:
- A comprehensive editor workspace combining a WYSIWYG/Markdown editor, AI-assisted ideation and outlining tools, an SEO panel, content scoring, and a publish scheduler.

What it aims to achieve:
- Quickly generate editorial ideas and outlines, draft high-quality content, optimize for search engines, assess content quality, and schedule/publish across multiple channels with version control and channel-specific previews.

Connected features and pages:
- Content Workflow & Publishing: End-to-end pipeline for ideation, drafting, revision, scheduling, multi-channel publishing, and versioning.
- Content Library: Centralized hub for drafts, published posts, scheduled items, and assets with filters by status, channel, or tag.
- Content Templates & SEO Snippets: Prebuilt templates and SEO snippets to accelerate AI-assisted content creation.
- Content Scheduler & Social Publisher: Calendar-based scheduling with manual and auto-scheduling modes; per-channel previews and queue management.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Rich Editor: Supports WYSIWYG and Markdown, with version history and inline AI-assisted suggestions.
- AI Idea & Outline Generator: Quick prompts to generate outlines, section headlines, and micro-outlines.
- SEO Panel: Keyword suggestions, readability score, title/meta preview, and on-page SEO checks.
- Content Scoring: Multi-metric scoring (completeness, relevance, readability, engagement) with actionable feedback.
- Scheduler: Date picker, time zone awareness, channels selector (blog, Twitter/X, LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, etc.), and pre-publish checklist.
- Publish Button: Unified action to publish immediately or schedule; include pre-flight checks and version capture.
- Visual style: Premium, professional, warm yellow accents with crisp white and neutral grays; mobile-first with scalable layouts, bottom navigation, FAB, and responsive cards.

API integrations:
- Local, in-app AI helpers (no external API required for this prompt; design should support API integration later).
- Optional: hooks for Supabase-backed data (posts, templates, drafts, channels) with safe access patterns.

Note: No external API endpoints are defined in this context, but ensure the architecture is ready for future API integration.

## Components to Build

- ContentEditorPanel
  - Rich text editor supporting WYSIWYG and Markdown
  - Version history and diff view
  - Inline AI suggestions and idea prompts
  - Outline drafting area with drag-to-reorder sections
  - Data-driven autosave with versioning

- AIIdeaOutlineGenerator
  - Quick prompts to generate content ideas, outlines, sections, and headlines
  - Accepts user context (topic, target persona, audience, tone)
  - Returns structured outline blocks and suggested headlines

- SEOPanel
  - Keyword suggestions (long-tail and short-tail)
  - Readability score (Flesch/Kincaid or custom metric)
  - Title and meta description preview with character limits
  - On-page SEO checks (alt text coverage, internal/external links, image optimization hints)
  - Suggestion chips to improve SEO

- ContentScoringPanel
  - Multi-metric scoring: Completeness, Relevance, Readability, Engagement Potential
  - Visual score gauge and breakdown
  - Actionable recommendations per metric

- SchedulerPanel
  - Publish date/time picker with time zone support
  - Channel selector with per-channel settings
  - Manual vs Auto-scheduling toggle
  - Pre-publish checklist (permissions, image approvals, links validation)

- PublishQueue & ChannelPreviews
  - Queue view for scheduled items with status, channel, and time
  - Per-channel previews (how content will look on each channel)

- ContentTemplatesLibrary
  - Prebuilt article templates and social post templates
  - SEO snippets and prompts for AI Assistant
  - Template editor to customize and save new templates

- ContentLibraryView
  - List of drafts, published pieces, scheduled posts, and assets
  - Filters by status, channel, or tag
  - Bulk actions (move, delete, duplicate, publish, schedule)
  - Detail drawer/panel for quick edit

- VersioningManager
  - Version history, compare, revert, and branch capability for complex edits

- AssetManager
  - Manage images, thumbnails, thumbnails generation hints, and alt text
  - Validation for image dimensions and file types

- UI/UX Components
  - CardLayout, BottomNav, FAB, Buttons (Primary/Secondary), Inputs (rounded with focus rings), Toggles, Selects, DateTime pickers, Chips, Tabs
  - Data Visualization: lightweight charts for content metrics and SEO insights

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks: React with TypeScript; state management via React Context or a lightweight store (e.g., Zustand).
- Type-safe: Use TypeScript types for PostDraft, PostVersion, Template, Channel, SEOStats, etc.
- State and Defaults:
  - useState<Array<T>>([]) for arrays; useState<YourType | null>(null) only when needed and guarded
  - Initialize all array-based state with [] and all objects with {} or null based on type
- Null-safety:
  - Guard all array operations: (items ?? []).map(...), Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - Access nested API-like objects with optional chaining
- Editor:
  - Implement a Rich Text Editor component with a toolbar, formatting options, bullet/number lists, headings, alignment, link insertion, and image embedding
  - Support inline AI-assisted ideas: render suggestion chips and insert content into the editor
  - Versioning: track changes and enable rollback to previous versions
- AI Integration Hooks (Abstracted):
  - useAiIdeaOutline(context) that returns { ideas, outline } and supports cancellation
  - useSeoSuggestions(content) that returns keywords, readability, title/meta suggestions
- Scheduling:
  - DateTime input with presets (Soon, Tomorrow, Next Week)
  - Timezone aware conversions
- Templates:
  - Render templates with placeholders and a preview pane
  - Ability to apply a template to the editor content
- Data Persistence:
  - Frontend state persists in local storage for unsaved changes; autosave every 30–60 seconds
  - Validation before publish (title length, required fields, image presence)
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA roles, keyboard navigability, label associations, color contrast checks

### Backend
- Not required to implement external APIs in this prompt, but define:
  - API surface for later integration:
    - GET /posts?status=&channel=&tag=
    - POST /posts (create draft)
    - PATCH /posts/{id} (update content, status, schedule)
    - POST /posts/{id}/publish (trigger publish)
    - GET /templates (content templates)
    - GET /channels (supported publish channels)
    - GET /versions/{postId} (version history)
  - Data models using Supabase-like conventions:
    - posts: id, title, content, status, channel, scheduled_at, version_id, seo, metrics
    - versions: id, post_id, content, timestamp, author_id
    - templates: id, type (article/social), content, seoSnippets
    - channels: id, name, platform, icon
    - assets: id, post_id, url, alt, width, height
- Data validation and safety:
  - Ensure all API responses are validated: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []

### Integration
- Component communication:
  - Editor emits onChange to update draft state
  - AIIdeaOutlineGenerator consumes current topic and persona; returns outline and ideas to insert
  - SEOPanel reads content and writes SEO metadata into a structured seo object
  - SchedulerPanel writes schedule to post object
  - TemplatesLibrary injects templates into editor context
  - ContentLibraryView consumes posts with filters and actions
- Data flow guards:
  - Always wrap data access with nullish coalescing and Array.isArray checks
- Versioning integration:
  - Every save creates a new version; provide diff and revert actions

## User Experience Flow
1) User lands on Content Editor & SEO Assistant.
2) User selects/enters topic, persona, tone, target audience; AIIdeaOutlineGenerator produces a scaffold outline and suggested headlines.
3) User uses AI suggestions to fill the outline; user edits content within Rich Text Editor; inline AI prompts provide suggestions while typing.
4) SEO Panel analyzes content in real-time, suggests keywords, readability improvements, and previews title/meta; user accepts suggestions or edits manually.
5) Content Scoring panel provides a multi-metric score with actionable recommendations; user iterates to improve score.
6) SchedulerPanel selects publish date/time, channels, and toggles manual/auto-scheduling; pre-publish checklist validates readiness.
7) User clicks Publish or Schedule; system creates a draft version, logs the change, and pushes to the queue or publishes to connected channels.
8) Upon publish/schedule, ContentLibraryView updates to reflect status; VersioningManager stores the new version; templates/assets are linked as needed.
9) User can view/restore previous versions, reuse templates, or clone drafts for new pieces.
10) All unsaved changes are autosaved locally; user can dismiss or restore from local storage if needed.

## Technical Specifications

Data Models (Schema Details)
- posts
  - id: string
  - title: string
  - content: string (rich text or markdown)
  - status: "draft" | "scheduled" | "published" | "archived"
  - channel_ids: string[] (IDs of connected channels)
  - scheduled_at: string | null (ISO date-time)
  - seo: {
      keywords: string[]
      title: string
      description: string
      readabilityScore: number
      metaTags: string[]
    }
  - metrics: { score: number; completeness: number; readability: number; engagementPotential: number }
  - version_id: string | null
  - created_at: string
  - updated_at: string
  - author_id: string
- versions
  - id: string
  - post_id: string
  - content: string
  - title: string
  - timestamp: string
  - author_id: string
- templates
  - id: string
  - type: "article" | "social"
  - name: string
  - content: string
  - seoSnippets: {
      keywords: string[]
      metaDescription: string
      titleTemplate: string
    }
- channels
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - platform: string
  - icon: string (or URL)
- assets
  - id: string
  - post_id: string
  - url: string
  - alt: string
  - width: number
  - height: number

API Endpoints (Routes and Methods)
- GET /posts?status=&channel=&tag=
- POST /posts
  - body: { title, content, channel_ids, scheduled_at, seo }
- PATCH /posts/{id}
  - body: { title?, content?, scheduled_at?, status?, seo? }
- POST /posts/{id}/publish
  - body: { channel_ids? }
- GET /templates
- GET /templates/{id}
- GET /channels
- GET /versions/{post_id}
- POST /versions
  - body: { post_id, content, title }

Security
- Authentication: JWT/OAuth2 tokens; all endpoints require valid authentication
- Authorization: Roles/permissions for content editor, editor, admin (e.g., canPublish, canSchedule)
- Data access: ensure user owns content or has explicit access rights
- Rate limiting for AI prompts and autosave to prevent abuse
- Data validation: server-side validation for all fields; respond with structured error messages

Validation
- Title: required, min 6, max 120 characters
- Content: required, min 20 characters
- Scheduled date: must be future date if status is scheduled
- SEO: keywords array non-empty; title/meta lengths within recommended ranges
- Channel IDs: array of string IDs, must map to existing channels
- Versions: maintain at least one version upon publish

